Sometimes things just don’t work out.
All you can do is laugh about it and move on.

Posting highlight reels and snippets of the best of the best is fun, but the reality is that sometimes things don’t go well or are unmitigated disasters.

As Rocky says,
“it ain’t how hard you hit; it’s about how hard you can get hit, and keep moving forward. How much you can take, and keep moving forward. That’s how winning is done.

So post some highlights and watch everyone crush it on social media. Just remember that real life ain’t all sunshine and rainbows.

✌️

Question:
Why take the long open shot in position 2?

Instead of going to 10 in last position. 

Port
Activate
Open

Pivot to
NS partial
Open
Popper
Swinger

Answer:
You are 100% correct in your stage breakdown and that would have been the most technically efficient way to shoot that stage. However, you aren’t factoring in risk and slower shooting to try and insure things didn’t go wrong while pushing the last mag to 10 with multiple steel and the swinger.
